# Abide Companion — environment variables
#
# =============================================================
#  SECURITY: never commit a real secret to this file or to .env.
#  `.env` is already in .dockerignore so it won't end up in the
#  container image, but if you use git, add `.env` to .gitignore
#  yourself. Treat LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY like a password.
# =============================================================
#
# Copy this file to `.env` in the same folder. Only the Langfuse keys
# are read from .env; Groq / Anthropic / OpenAI keys are entered by
# the user in the browser UI (gear icon, bottom-right) and stored in
# the browser's localStorage.
#
# Langfuse is OPTIONAL. If the keys below are left blank the server
# still runs normally — you just don't get observability traces.

# Get keys from https://cloud.langfuse.com (free tier is enough).
# Paste the real values into .env — NEVER into this .env.example file,
# which is meant to be checked in as a template.
LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY=
LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY=

# Region endpoint. Use:
#   https://us.cloud.langfuse.com   for the US region
#   https://cloud.langfuse.com      for the EU region (default)
#   (self-hosted URL)               for a self-hosted instance
LANGFUSE_BASE_URL=https://cloud.langfuse.com
